-oil"><img src="//www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/styles/bbcgf_thumbnail_search/public/glossary/NEW-sunflower-oil%20IGNORE.jpg?itok=QlNpoo1a" width="100" height="100" alt="Sunflower oil" title="Sunflower oil" /></a></div><h2 class="node-title node-glossary-title"><a href="/glossary/sunflower-oil">Sunflower oil</a></h2><p>A variety of oils can be used for baking. Sunflower is the one we use most often at Good Food asâ€¦</p> </article></span></li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="2 red onions, roots trimmed and cut into eighths">2 red onions, roots trimmed and cut into eighths</li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="2 large pears, quartered and cored (leave the skin on)">2 large <a href="/glossary/pear" class="ingredients-list__glossary-link" data-tooltip-content="#ingredients-glossary--2 &gt; article" data-tooltip-width="350" data-tooltip-hide-delay="200" data-tooltip-flyout="true">pears</a>, quartered and cored (leave the skin on)<span class="ingredients-list__glossary-element" id="ingredients-glossary--2"><article id="node-259496" role="main" class="node node-glossary-item node-teaser node-teaser clearfix main row grid-padding"><div class="node-image"> <a href="/glossary/pear"><img src="//www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/styles/bbcgf_thumbnail_search/public/glossary/pear.jpg?itok=8jnzLE04" width="100" height="100" alt="Pear" title="Like apples, to which they are related, pears come in thousands of varieties" /></a></div><h2 class="node-title node-glossary-title"><a href="/glossary/pear">Pear</a></h2> <span class="fonetic text-style-alt">pair</span><p>Like apples, to which they are related, pears come in thousands of varieties, of which only aâ€¦</p> </article></span></li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="few sprigs rosemary, leaves roughly chopped">few sprigs <a href="/glossary/rosemary" class="ingredients-list__glossary-link" data-tooltip-content="#ingredients-glossary--3 &gt; article" data-tooltip-width="350" data-tooltip-hide-delay="200" data-tooltip-flyout="true">rosemary</a>, leaves roughly chopped<span class="ingredients-list__glossary-element" id="ingredients-glossary--3"><article id="node-257917" role="main" class="node node-glossary-item node-teaser node-teaser clearfix main row grid-padding"><div class="node-image"> <a href="/glossary/rosemary"><img src="//www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/styles/bbcgf_thumbnail_search/public/glossary/rosemary.jpg?itok=Fl08LLg1" width="100" height="100" alt="Rosemary" title="Rosemary has traditionally been paired with lamb, chicken and game, but it&#039;s also suited to fish and bean dishes" /></a></div><h2 class="node-title node-glossary-title"><a href="/glossary/rosemary">Rosemary</a></h2> <span class="fonetic text-style-alt"> rose-mar-ee</span><p>Rosemary's intense, fragrant aroma has traditionally been paired with lamb, chicken and gameâ€¦</p> </article></span></li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="4 pork steaks, about 175g/6oz each, trimmed of excess fat">4 <a href="/glossary/pork" class="ingredients-list__glossary-link" data-tooltip-content="#ingredients-glossary--4 &gt; article" data-tooltip-width="350" data-tooltip-hide-delay="200" data-tooltip-flyout="true">pork</a> steaks, about 175g/6oz each, trimmed of excess fat<span class="ingredients-list__glossary-element" id="ingredients-glossary--4"><article id="node-260636" role="main" class="node node-glossary-item node-teaser node-teaser clearfix main row grid-padding"><div class="node-image"> <a href="/glossary/pork"><img src="//www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/styles/bbcgf_thumbnail_search/public/glossary/pork.jpg?itok=qx3IxWW9" width="100" height="100" alt="Pork" title="One of the most versatile types of meat, pork is economical, tender if cooked correctly, and oozing with flavour" /></a></div><h2 class="node-title node-glossary-title"><a href="/glossary/pork">Pork</a></h2> <span class="fonetic text-style-alt">paw-k</span><p>One of the most versatile types of meat, pork is economical, tender if cooked correctly, andâ€¦</p> </article></span></li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="50g blue cheese, cubed">50g blue cheese, cubed</li></ul></div></div> </section> <section id="recipe-method" class="responsive-tabs__pane"><h2 class="responsive-tabs__pane-title">Method</h2><div class="method"><ol class="method__list"><li class="method__item" itemprop="recipeInstructions"><p>Heat the oil in a roasting tin on the hob (use 2 rings), then add the onions, pears, most of the rosemary and seasoning. Fry for 5 mins or until just starting to caramelise.</p></li><li class="method__item" itemprop="recipeInstructions"><p>Heat grill to high. Season the pork, then arrange among the veg and fry for 5 mins, turning halfway until golden and cooked through. Scatter with the remaining rosemary and the cheese, grill until the cheese starts to melt, then serve.</p></li></ol></div> <footer class="recipe-info"><div class="recipe-info__publication">Recipe from Good Food magazine, <a href="/search/recipes/date/1170288000" class="text-style-alt">February 2007</a></div> <a class="recipe-info__magazine-ad" href=" https://www.buysubscriptions.com/print/bbc-good-food-magazine-subscription?promo=GFBS718&style=Brand&utm_medium=brandsite&utm_source=bbcgoodfood.com&utm_campaign=recipe_GFBS718_Brand&utm_content=recipe-banner" rel="external" onclick="Drupal.GFAnalytics.trackEvent(['Magazines', 'subscribe', 'Recipe' ])"> <img src="https://www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/magazine/gf_aug18_337x109.jpg" alt="BBC GoodFood Magazine" /> </a> </footer> </section></div></div> <section id="block-bbcgf-search-views-bbcgf-cc-rel-recipes" class="section-box section-box--you-may-also-like"> <header class="section-box__header"><h2 class="section-box__title">You may also like</h2> </header><div class="section-box__content"><div class="carousel"><div cl